Greece Plans to Boost Revenue at Hellinikon, OPAP, Euro2day Says

-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 
2011-03-14T08:05:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/greece-plans-to-boost-revenue-at-hellinikon-opap-euro2day-says.html
Greece’s Finance Ministry plans to
this week appoint advisers for raising revenue from Athens
International Airport, Hellinikon airport and  Opap SA (OPAP) , Euro2day
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  The government aims to raise 200 million euros ($279
million) to 300 million euros by extending the lease with  Hochtief AG (HOT)  to operate Athens International and 5 billion euros
to 8 billion euros from exploiting the site of Hellinikon
airport, which Athens International replaced, the news website
said.  The government also plans to generate revenue by extending
Opap’s concession on sport betting in Greece, Euro2day said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marcus Bensasson in Athens at 
 mbensasson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net . 